ZCZC EE08
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 092300 UTC
FRIDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED OVER FRANCE 1038. THIS WILL
GRADUALLY MOV E TO BE CENTRED OVER EERN EUROPE BY THE END OF THE PERIOD.
IN THE MEANTIME A DEEP LOW WILL DEVELOP IN THE ATLANTIC INITIALLY CENTRED
TO THE SW OF ICELAND ON FRIDAY EVENING. THIS WILL MIGRATE TOWARD THE BRITISH
ISLES THROUGH SATURDAY BECMG CENTRED CLOSE TO THE NORWEGIAN COAST BY MIDDAY
SUNDAY WITH A DAUGHTER LOW BECMG DEVELOPED NEAR THE IRISH SEA. THIS LOW
IS THEN FCST TO MOV E ACROSS THE UK INTO THE N SEA FOR MONDAY. A TRANSIENT
RIDGE THEN AFFECTS THE UK AHEAD OF THE NXT ATLANTIC LOW WHICH APPROACHES
THE W LATER MONDAY. STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS WITH OCCASIONAL GALES
WILL MOV E ACROSS THE N NITON FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY. WINDS BRIEFLY
EASING IN THE W OVERNIGHT BUT FURTHER STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS MOV
E SUNDAY AND AGAIN MONDAY WITH A CHANCE OF ISOL GALES
